response.overview: Dream Ninety-Three follows a figure suspended between reality and dream, moving through daily life only partially present, as if consciousness has slipped out of alignment. Their inner monologue speaks in a woman’s voice, unsettling identity and suggesting the film unfolds inside an unseen mind. As inner and outer worlds blur, the figure falls inward—into a bowl of split pea soup—an absurd yet intimate image hinting at wholeness. The film resists resolution, lingering in the space between.
response.title: Dream Ninety-Three
